{"id":"262296502_The_Exact_Online_String_Matching_Problem_A_Review_of_the_Most_Recent_Results","abstract":"This article addresses the online exact string matching problem which consists in finding all occurrences of a given pattern p in a text t. It is an extensively studied problem in computer science, mainly due to its direct applications to such diverse areas as text, image and signal processing, speech analysis and recognition, information retrieval, data compression, computational biology and chemistry.\nIn the last decade more than 50 new algorithms have been proposed for the problem, which add up to a wide set of (almost 40) algorithms presented before 2000. In this article we review the string matching algorithms presented in the last decade and present experimental results in order to bring order among the dozens of articles published in this area.","authors":["Simone Faro","Thierry Lecroq"],"meta":["February 2013ACM Computing Surveys 45(2)","DOI:10.1145/2431211.2431212"],"references":["280851530_A_fast_implementation_of_the_Boyer-Moore_string_matching_algorithm","267387910_Fast_Variants_of_Bit_Parallel_Approach_to_Suffix_Automata","262349834_Two-way_string-matching","226574953_Speeding_up_two_string-matching_algorithms","226574739_A_Simple_Fast_Hybrid_Pattern-Matching_Algorithm","221580191_Alternative_Algorithms_for_Bit-Parallel_String_Matching","221579961_Practical_and_Optimal_String_Matching","221544113_A_Method_to_Overcome_Computer_Word_Size_Limitation_in_Bit-Parallel_Pattern_Matching","221513115_Factor_Oracle_A_New_Structure_for_Pattern_Matching","221313692_Real-Time_String_Matching_in_Sublinear_Space","221276861_Bit-Parallelism2_Getting_to_the_Next_Level_of_Parallelism","221241652_Filter_Based_Fast_Matching_of_Long_Patterns_by_Using_SIMD_Instructions","221241593_Efficient_Variants_of_the_Backward-Oracle-Matching_Algorithm","221131658_Fast-Search_A_New_Efficient_Variant_of_the_Boyer-Moore_String_Matching_Algorithm","220982041_Tuning_BNDM_with_q-grams",